The Durban University of Technology has closed five campuses, following an invasion prompted by a fake social media post. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The Durban University of Technology has closed all of its five campuses. This was triggered by the invasion of a large crowd of students and prospective students at the university's main campus. They say they were invited by a social media post to register on campus. READ: DUT campuses closed with immediate effect The post was later confirmed by the university as fake. Earlier on Wednesday, police used tear gas to disperse the crowd. eNCA's Thuba Vilane shares more details in the video above.